<h3> Current research projects</h3><br>
<a href="http://www.dspivak.net/grants/AFOSR2020-Topos-ContextDependence.pdf">Functorial Dynamics and Interaction.</a> 
Using polynomial functors to model dynamical systems, decision processes, data migration, and more! 
(I'm completely enthralled with the category Poly.)

A <a href="https://github.com/dspivak/poly/">book</a> on the subject is in preparation. Idris code can be found 
<a href="https://github.com/ToposInstitute/poly/blob/main/code-examples/poly_up_to_fibonacci.idr">here</a>. 

<br><br>
<a href="./grants/AFOSR2022-Structure_and_Dynamics_of_Working_Language.pdf">
Structure and dynamics of working language</a> Using polynomial functors 
to account for how language works, in the sense of physics. This grant has been recommended for funding, but has not yet started.

