<h3> Past research subjects</h3><br>

<a href="./grants/index.html">Applied Category Theory</a>. Various ACT grants, some funded and others not.<br><br>

<a href="http://math.mit.edu/~dspivak/dman"> Derived manifolds</a>. The 
category of derived manifolds contains arbitrary intersections of 
manifolds, even if they are not transverse, while retaining enough 
structure so that every compact derived manifold has a fundamental class 
in cobordism.<br><br>

<a href="http://dspivak.net/qcmap.pdf"> Mapping spaces in 
quasi-categories</a>. Joint work with <a 
href="http://uoregon.edu/~ddugger"> Dan Dugger</a>.  <br><br>

<a href="./afsf.pdf"> Anomaly-free sets of fermions</a>. A 
physics paper I coauthored with <a
href="http://www.slac.stanford.edu/spires/find/hep/www?rawcmd=ea+Batra,+Puneet">
Puneet
Batra </a> and <a
href="http://www.slac.stanford.edu/spires/find/hep/www?rawcmd=ea+Dobrescu,+Bogdan+A">
Bogdan Dobrescu</a>.<br><br>
<a href="http://dspivak.net/metric_realization090922.pdf"> Metric realization of fuzzy simplicial sets</a> 
A draft I never published, and may contain errors, but which has gotten some attention from the creators of <a "https://arxiv.org/abs/1802.03426">UMAP</a> and others.
